9 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to schools; requiring the State
Department of Education to create and manage a
11 database of all school support employees; providing
database content requirements; requiring school
12 districts to annually submit certain information to
the Department by certain date; requiring information
13 to be certified annually by certain date; requiring
updates to certain information; providing for
14 codification; and providing an effective date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-103.16 of Title 70, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. The State Department of Education shall create and manage a
22 database for registering all school support employees as defined in
23 Section 1-116 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The database
24
Req. No. 3906 Page 1

1 may be administered within or integrated with existing educator
2 certification or personnel tracking systems of the Department.
3 B. For each school support employee, the database shall
4 include:
5 1. The full legal name of the support employee;
6 2. The name of the employing school district and school site
7 including the employee’s position or role; and
8 3. A unique, permanent identification number issued by the
9 Department that shall be used to identify the support employee for
10 employment verification and record continuity across school
11 districts and other employment records maintained by the Department.
12 The identification number shall not be reassigned or altered due to
13 a change in employing school district or subsequent employment
14 within the public education system of this state.
15 C. No later than October 1, 2027, and by October 1 annually
16 thereafter, each school district shall submit the information
17 required in paragraphs 1 and 2 of subsection B of this section to
18 the Department for all employed support personnel. Corrections and
19 updates may be made until October 15 annually when the submitted
20 information shall be certified by the school district
21 superintendent.
22 D. Each school district shall update the information required
23 by this section within thirty (30) days of hiring a new support
24
Req. No. 3906 Page 2

1 empl oyee and within thirty (30) days of a support employee’s
2 termination or other separation from employment.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
